{"id":14881455,"mediaExerciseId":"2e4939d4-07cf-4533-b2ba-500c8f0bc27d","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":612388,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":488,"solutions":[{"id":5981803,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"First, we have to find out the cost of equity which we denote with $CE$, where the dividend per share $DS$ is $\\$2.35$, growth rate $GR$ is $4.1\\%$ and the stock sells $S$ is $\\$43$\n\n$$\\begin{align*} \nCE&=\\frac{DS \\times (1+GR)}{S}+GR\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{2.35 \\times (1+4.1\\%)}{43}+4.1\\%\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{2.35 \\times (1+0.041)}{43}+0.041\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{2.35 \\times 1.041}{43}+0.041\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{2.446}{43}+0.041\\\\[12pt]\n&=0.0978\\\\[7pt]\n&=9.78\\%\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nTherefore, the cost of equity is $\\boxed{9.78\\%}$\n \n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Second, we have to find out the cost of equity capital which we denote with $C$,  where the current yielding $CY$ is $3.4\\%$, the beta $B$ is $1.05$ and the risk premium $RP$ is $7\\%$\n\n$$\\begin{align*} \nC&=CY+(B\\times RP)\\\\[7pt]\n&=3.4\\%+ (1.05 \\times 7\\%)\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.034+ (1.05\\times 0.07)\\\\[7ptt]\n&=0.034 +0.0735\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.1075\\\\[7pt]\n&=10.75\\%\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nTherefore, the cost of equity capital is $\\boxed{10.75\\%}$\nâ€‹\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Finally, let's find out the best estimate which we denote with $BE$, where the cost of equity capital $C$ is $10.75\\%$ and the cost of equity $CE$ is $9.78\\%$\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nBE&=\\frac{C+CE}{2}\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{10.75\\%+9.78\\%}{2}\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{0.1075+0.0978}{2}\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{0.2053}{2}\\\\[12pt]\n&=0.1026\\\\[12pt]\n&=10.26\\%\n\\end{align*}$$ \n\nTherefore, the best estimate is $\\boxed{10.26\\%}$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"$\\boxed{10.26\\%}$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":44,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/fc9483429dfd8f413074a0c74aca2439/79ab4917a8304ce974e7bb439da9d69e/lateximg_large.png","width":114},"regular":{"height":22,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/fc9483429dfd8f413074a0c74aca2439/79ab4917a8304ce974e7bb439da9d69e/lateximg.png","width":57}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"7fbbcf19-6b9c-4682-946b-b094a33fe191","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881456,"exerciseName":"4","page":488,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"9116208b-af2c-4872-8384-05b053be2891","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-14-questions-and-problems-4-9116208b-af2c-4872-8384-05b053be2891"},{"id":14881457,"exerciseName":"5","page":488,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"c3c25741-dd51-43eb-8997-16f4a9163a90","_webUrl":"ht